   <taskbody>
      <prereq class="- topic/section task/prereq ">
         <ul class="- topic/ul ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">Mail merge is configured for the form. <ph product="Exclude_PG_Content" class="- topic/ph ">For additional information, refer to <xref href="../../Library_Management/Standard_Library_Catalogs/Notifications/ConfigMailMerge.dita"
                        class="- topic/xref ">Configuring Mail Merge</xref>.</ph>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">Mail body templates are available in the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Mail Body Templates</uicontrol> catalog of the library. <ph product="Exclude_PG_Content" class="- topic/ph ">For additional information, refer to <xref href="../../Library_Management/Standard_Library_Catalogs/Notifications/MailBodyTemps.dita"
                        class="- topic/xref ">Creating Mail Body Templates</xref>.</ph>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">You must be invited to the project and assigned with the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">View</uicontrol> permission.</li>
         </ul>
      </prereq>
      <context class="- topic/section task/context ">You can send email notifications after configuring Mail Merge for the form. The mail merge documentis sent as an attachment.</context>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">On the required list page, select the records the details of which must be sent to recipients.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Mail Merge</uicontrol>, and then click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Merge and Email</uicontrol>.
</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">The <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Merge and Email</uicontrol> dialog box is displayed.</info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Recipient(s)</uicontrol> box, perform the following steps to select email recipients:</cmd>
            <substeps class="- topic/ol task/substeps ">
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click <image href="../../Icons/select.png"
                            class="- topic/image "
                            placement="inline">
                        <alt class="- topic/alt ">List</alt>
                     </image> to select the required recipients.
</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">The <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Recipients</uicontrol> dialog box is displayed.
</info>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">The dialog box lists all the users of the application. <ph product="Exclude_PG_Content" class="- topic/ph ">For information on user accounts, refer to <xref href="../../CoSP/Administration/User_Management/User_Accounts/Creating_User_Account/CreateUserAcc.dita"
                              class="- topic/xref ">Creating a User Account</xref>.</ph>
                  </info>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Select the required recipients, and then click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Select</uicontrol>.
</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">Alternatively, you can enter the email addresses of the recipients. You can enter multiple email addresses separated by a semicolon (;).</info>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">From the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Mail Merge Configuration</uicontrol> drop-down list, select the required configuration.
</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">The available options are all the mail merge configurations associated with the form. <ph product="Exclude_PG_Content" class="- topic/ph ">For information on mail merge configurations, refer to <xref href="../../Library_Management/Standard_Library_Catalogs/Notifications/ConfigMailMerge.dita"
                              class="- topic/xref ">Configuring Mail Merge</xref>.</ph>
                  </info>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">From the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Mail Body Template</uicontrol> drop-down list, select the required template.

</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">Available options are mail body templates defined in the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Mail Body Templates</uicontrol> catalog of the library.</info>
                  <info product="Exclude_PG_Content" class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">For additional information, refer to <xref href="../../Library_Management/Standard_Library_Catalogs/Notifications/MailBodyTemps.dita"
                           class="- topic/xref ">Creating Mail Body Templates</xref>.</info>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">To send the mail merge document in PDF format, select the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Convert to PDF</uicontrol> check box to convert the mail merge document to PDF.  If the check box is cleared, then the mail merge document is sent in the Word format.</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                     <note class="- topic/note "> If the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Convert to PDF</uicontrol> check box is selected at the time mail merge is configured, then this check box is selected by default. Clear the check box if conversion of the mail merge document to PDF is not required.</note>
                  </info>
               </substep>
            </substeps>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Send</uicontrol>.
</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">The email with the mail merge document as attachment is sent to the selected recipients. If multiple records are selected, then separate emails for each record is sent to the recipients.</info>
         </step>
      </steps>
